  "body": "\r\n## Issue\r\n\r\nWhen running a test that expects a require(..) condition to fail, the require failure is not handled correctly in Truffle v5.1.5 and later. This works correctly in v5.1.4 and earlier.\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\nPlease see bug POC at https://github.com/cfelde/truffle-requirebug\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nTest should pass.\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\nTest does not pass.\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System: Mac\r\n\r\nTruffle v5.1.5 (core: 5.1.5)\r\nSolidity v0.5.12 (solc-js)\r\nNode v13.3.0\r\nWeb3.js v1.2.1\r\n",
